Name: Spotted Duck
Description: Eat Icecream and watch ducks. Local Icecream Tastings. Has coffee, rootbeer, lemonade

Name: Bellhurst Castle
Description: Its a castle and winery! (Easter brunch baffet) as an option, otherwise it has some bar food and some sit down food. Meat is expensive but other than that normal prices with cheapish drinks.

Name: Ports Cafe
Hours: 5pm - 9pm (10 pm F & Sa, Closed Su & M)

Name: Au Bon Pain
Description: Closed saturdays. Quick Bite. Seems like a panera and serves soups, salads and sandwiches. Can order ahead of time.

Name: Opus
Description: Serves breakfast, espresso, smoothies, tea, pizza, salads, sandwiches and wraps.

Name: Seneca Harbor Station
Description: A little expensive, old train station

Name: Silverbird Woodfired
Description: Serves pizza, burgers, salads, chicken fingers, some seafood, lots of options

Name: Penn Yan Diner
Description: It says it has the best pancakes and homefries

Name: FLX Wienery
Description: Cayla will probably go here a lot! Quick bite. Wieners, sausages, fresh burgers, fries

Name: Oak Leaf Cafe
Description: All types of food. You can buy stuff in bulk if needed.
